1. Legacy Software Risks
The versions of Skype provided here (5.x - 7.x) are "End-of-Life" (EOL). This means they no longer receive security patches or bug fixes from Microsoft. 
Vulnerabilities: Older software often contains known security flaws that hackers can exploit to steal data or install malware.
No Support: Since these versions are retired, Microsoft will not offer any help or technical support if something goes wrong. 
